HEADWORD: Suradanni
<hw>Su`ra*dan"ni</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A valuable kind
of wood obtained on the shores of the Demerara River in South America,
much used for timbers, rails, naves and fellies of wheels, and the
like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

